# Wire the Waitlist to a Google Sheet

This is a zero-cost, no-backend setup. Every submission on the landing page lands in a Sheet you own. Takes about 5 minutes the first time.

## What's already done (the code side)

- `index.html` — `submitWL()` rewritten to POST the form data to a URL you'll paste in. Has loading state, duplicate-safe, and shows a network-error message if the POST fails.
- `apps-script/Code.gs` — the server-side script that receives the POST and writes a row to your Sheet. De-duplicates by email. Adds headers on first run.

## What you do (the Google side)

### 1. Create the Sheet

- Go to https://sheets.new (creates a blank sheet instantly, logged-in Google account).
- Rename the file to `CitiMore Waitlist` (top-left, click the title).
- Leave the default tab empty — the script creates the `Waitlist` tab on first submission.

### 2. Open the Apps Script editor

- In the Sheet's menu: **Extensions → Apps Script**.
- A new tab opens with a file called `Code.gs` containing `function myFunction() {}`.

### 3. Paste the script

- Open `citimore-site/apps-script/Code.gs` from this project.
- Select all, copy.
- In the Apps Script editor, select all of the placeholder code, delete it, and paste ours in.
- Click the floppy-disk **Save** icon (or `Cmd+S`). Name the project `CitiMore Waitlist API` when prompted.

### 4. Deploy as a Web App

- Top-right, click **Deploy → New deployment**.
- Click the gear icon next to "Select type" → choose **Web app**.
- Fill in:
  - **Description:** `CitiMore waitlist endpoint`
  - **Execute as:** `Me (your-email@gmail.com)`
  - **Who has access:** `Anyone`  ← this is required so the public form can POST to it
- Click **Deploy**.
- First time only: Google asks you to authorize. Click **Authorize access** → pick your account → click **Advanced → Go to CitiMore Waitlist API (unsafe)** → **Allow**. (This "unsafe" warning appears for all unverified personal scripts — it's fine because you wrote it.)
- Copy the **Web app URL** — it looks like `https://script.google.com/macros/s/AKfy.../exec`. This is your endpoint.

### 5. Paste the URL into the site

- Open `citimore-site/index.html`.
- Find the line (search for `WAITLIST_ENDPOINT`):
  ```js
  const WAITLIST_ENDPOINT = 'PASTE_YOUR_APPS_SCRIPT_WEB_APP_URL_HERE';
  ```
- Replace the placeholder with the URL you copied. Save.

### 6. Test locally

- Open `index.html` in a browser (double-click, or `npx serve .`).
- Scroll to the waitlist, fill it in, hit submit.
- Flip to your Sheet — you should see a new row in a freshly-created `Waitlist` tab with all the fields.
- If nothing appears: open DevTools → Console. You'll see `[CitiMore Waitlist] submit failed` with the error. Most common causes: the URL wasn't pasted correctly, or the deployment access is set to "Only myself" instead of "Anyone".

### 7. Deploy to Vercel

- Once the local test works, push to Vercel (`vercel --prod` from the `citimore-site` folder, or push to GitHub).
- Do one more live test against the production URL to confirm.

