## Updating the script later

- If you tweak `Code.gs`, you **must click Deploy → Manage deployments → (pencil icon) → Version: New version → Deploy** again — Apps Script doesn't re-deploy on save.
- The URL stays the same across new versions of the same deployment, so you don't need to update `index.html`.

## Reading the live count on the page (optional, later)

The script also responds to `GET` with a real count. If you want the `412` placeholder to become real on page load, add this near the top of the script block in `index.html`:

```js
fetch(WAITLIST_ENDPOINT).then(r => r.json()).then(d => {
  if (d && typeof d.count === 'number') {
    count = d.count;
    ['wl-count','hero-count','sticky-count'].forEach(id => {
      const el = document.getElementById(id); if (el) el.textContent = count;
    });
  }
}).catch(() => {});
```

## Hardening for production

- **Rate-limit:** add a honeypot hidden input `<input name="company" style="display:none">` and in `doPost` reject if `e.parameter.company` is non-empty. Blocks ~95% of bots.
- **Email the team on new signups:** at the end of `doPost`, add
  ```js
  MailApp.sendEmail('hello@citimore.ng', 'New CitiMore signup', email + '  (' + params.type + ')');
  ```
- **Double opt-in:** send a confirmation email via Resend / SendGrid / Gmail-from-Apps-Script with a unique confirm link (needs a bit more code — ask me and I'll scaffold it).
- **Privacy:** add a one-liner under the email input: "We'll only email you about CitiMore launch updates. Your data is stored in our Google Sheet and is NDPR-protected."

## Troubleshooting quick table

| Symptom | Cause | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| "Network error — please try again" in the form | `WAITLIST_ENDPOINT` still has the placeholder, or URL is wrong | Paste the correct `/exec` URL. |
| Form looks like it worked but Sheet stays empty | Deployment access isn't "Anyone" | Deploy → Manage deployments → edit → set access to Anyone. |
| "Authorization required" error in DevTools | Script wasn't authorized during Deploy step | Re-run the Deploy flow and click through the authorization screens. |
| Duplicate submissions from the same email aren't appended | Working as designed (de-dup by email). | Remove the `emailExists_` check in `Code.gs` if you don't want de-dup. |
